description:
Giggle Comics is an American comics anthology. It was originally published by Creston Publications, which became an imprint of American Comics Group (ACG) in 1943. Giggle Comics had many stories with funny animals, mirroring a wider trend.

Giggle Comics was published under the Creston imprint for issues #1-63; issues #64-onward were under the ACG name. The title published 99 issues, from Oct. 1943 - Jan. 1955, when it changed its name to Spencer Spook, publishing two more issues before finally being cancelled in June 1955.
name: Giggle Comics

description:
Ha Ha and Giggle were anthology titles that targeted a young audience who were read to by adults, older friends, or siblings, or were just beginning to read themselves. Features changed with each issue, but talking animals dominated the books. The stories were simple with a single theme and employed mostly visual humor. Human faces were rare.

Published from October 1943 to January 1955 with 99 total issues numbered 1- 99.

Continues as Teepee Tim (1955 series) #100-102.
name: Ha Ha Comics

description:
Publication Info

Written by Mark Waid with art by Barry Kitson and James Pascoe, Empire is an American comic book series originally published by Image imprint Gorilla Comics, Empire was acquired by DC Comics. The two Gorilla issues were reprinted in Empire #0, and were followed by a six-issue limited series. The book carries a "Suggested for Mature Readers" warning. The series has also been collected in a 208-page trade paperback.

Story

Empire is set in a dystopian future in which the Earth has been conquered by an armored supervillain named Golgoth. After a decade of stamping out pockets of resistance, Golgoth is now confronted with betrayal from within as well as an insurrection supported by an alien race known as the Qaron. Establishing a cabinet of Ministers,Golgoth ensures their loyalty through addiction to a booster drug called Eucharist, which is secretly harvested directly from the corpse of Golgoth's late nemesis, the heroic Endymion. The series is framed through the perspective of Delphi, Golgoth's daughter, as well as Gologth himself and the multiple perspectives of his Ministers. Intrigue and action abound throughout this series.

Awards

Empire was nominated for an Eisner Award in 2004 for "Best Limited Series."

Collected in Empire.
name: Empire

30 Days of Night was one of the undisputed success stories of modern comics, spawning a bestselling trade paperback, a major motion picture deal, and the attention of thousands of fans longing for an innovative tale of terror. Now the same creative team revisits Barrow, Alaska, the town where it all began, as the long night creeps once more over the tundra. Some things may have changed, but the horror remains...

description:
In a sleepy, secluded Alaska town called Barrow, the sun sets and doesn't rise for over thirty consecutive days and nights. From the darkness, across the frozen wasteland, an evil will come that will bring the residents of Barrow to their knees. The only hope for the town is the Sheriff and Deputy, husband and wife who are torn between their own survival and saving the town they love.

Collected Editions

description:
30 Days of Night was one of the bestselling trade paperbacks of 2003, picked up a nomination for the prized International Horror Guild Award, and helped to usher in a new era for horror comics. Dark Days, the sequel to that riveting vampire story, won its creators a new set of accolades and cemented their standing at the front of the pack of horror maestros in the comics field. In Dark Days, the action shifts from Barrow, Alaska to L.A., as Stella Olemaun, her life forever altered by the vampires' assault, rededicates herself to wiping out vampires and alerting the world to their shadowed existence. Along the way she meets new allies and new foeslots and lots of foes. Intense action and gripping suspense make this the must-have horror book of the season.

description:
The New Invaders Volume 1

A series about a new team of Invaders forming, hence the name. The series started with a special issue 0, that on itself was part of a continued story from Avengers Vol.3 issues 82, 83 and 84. That story focuses on the formation of the team. The series however ran for only 10 issues (9 regular with one issue 0). It has been collected into a trade paperback entitled New Invaders: To End All Wars.
name: The New Invaders

description:
From the pages of Alias, comes this series! From the point of view of the Bugle writers and Jessica Jones, this story tells what happens at the Bugle when J. Jonah Jameson realizes that his point of view on the super heroes is dragging his paper down. No one reads anymore, any source of news can be found else where. So Jameson decides to do something that will bring the readers back, The Pulse. The Pulse is suppose to be a column that tells us what is happening in the lives of super heroes. Ben Urich working with former costumed super hero Jessica Jones to get all the inside stories, including the exclusive on Jessica's pregnancy with super hero for hire Luke Cage.

Collected Editions

  • Jessica Jones: The Pulse - The Complete Collection (#1-9 & 11-14)
  • The Pulse: Thin Air (#1-6)
  • The Pulse: Secret War (#7-9)
  • House of M: World of M Featuring Wolverine (#10)
  • The Pulse: Fear (#11-14)

Translated into Spanish.
name: The Pulse

description:
The fourth iteration of Swamp Thing, this series was written by three writers, Andy Diggle (#1-6), Will Pfeifer (#7-8) and Joshua Dysart (#9-29) and shifted the focus back to Swamp Thing himself whereas the previous series had been about his daughter (though she played a significant role in this series as well). The main artist for the series was Enrique Breccia (#1-6, 9-12, 15-18, 21-24, 27-29) but sprinkled throughout his run were Richard Corben (#7-8, 20), Timothy Green II (#13-14), Ronald Wimberly (#19), Dean Ormston (#25) and Jock (#26). Lasting for twenty-nine issues, the series was eventually cancelled due to low sales.

Trade Paperbacks

  • #01-06: Bad Seed
  • #09-14: Love in Vain
  • #15-20: Healing the Breach
name: Swamp Thing
